{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-17T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When the sun sets, a mysterious animal takes over the skies: bats. With more than 1,400 species found on every continent except Antarctica, they play a vital role in keeping ecosystems in balance. They have existed for over 50 million years, and while only three species feed on blood, the vast majority rely on insects, fruit, nectar or pollen, helping to control pests and support plant life.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_ROW6773514789_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.FlyingFoxMom_ROW6773514789_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Grey-headed flying fox carrying her pup, Yarra Bend Park, Australia","Copyright":"© Doug Gimesy/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Grey-headed+flying+fox&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260417_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260417_FlyingFoxMom"},"Ssd":"20260417","Name":"FlyingFoxMom","Market":"ROW","Hash":"6773514789","FullDateString":"17 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Each spring, Skagit Valley in Washington, United States, transforms into a patchwork of colour that celebrates the arrival of bloom season. Throughout April, visitors explore tulip gardens and farmland lined with vibrant rows of flowers, all framed by mountain views. The valley's fertile soils, shaped by centuries of sediment from the Skagit River, make it one of the most productive agricultural regions in the Pacific Northwest. Tulips arrived here in the early twentieth century when farmers realised the cool springs and long daylight hours were ideal for growing bulbs.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_ROW2420005352_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SkagitTulips_ROW2420005352_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Skagit Valley Tulip Fields, Washington, United States","Copyright":"© Alan Majchrowicz/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Skagit+Valley+Washington&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260416_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260416_SkagitTulips"},"Ssd":"20260416","Name":"SkagitTulips","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2420005352","FullDateString":"16 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Set in the foothills and front ranges of the Canadian Rockies, Kananaskis Country stretches across a vast network of protected valleys, dense forests and alpine peaks. Located in Alberta, the region was formally established in 1978, uniting several provincial parks and protected areas under a shared vision of conservation. Clear rivers cut through limestone cliffs, while spruce and pine forests rise toward high mountain passes.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AlbertaSnowMts_ROW3394188074_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AlbertaSnowMts_ROW3394188074_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Pine trees reflected in the Forgetmenot Pond in Kananaskis Country, Alberta, Canada","Copyright":"© chinaface/Getty images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260415_AlbertaSnowMts\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Kananaskis+Country+Alberta&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260415_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260415_AlbertaSnowMts"},"Ssd":"20260415","Name":"AlbertaSnowMts","Market":"ROW","Hash":"3394188074","FullDateString":"15 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Sea anemones may look like underwater flowers, but they're actually animals—close relatives of jellyfish and corals. Anchored to rocks or reefs, they use a sticky base and a crown of waving tentacles armed with tiny stingers to capture passing prey. Those stings can paralyse small fish, yet one famous neighbour is immune.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_ROW2121702907_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OcellarisClownfish_ROW2121702907_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Common clownfish in a sea anemone, Raja Ampat Islands, Indonesia","Copyright":"© Magnus Lundgren/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260414_OcellarisClownfish\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sea+anemone&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260414_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260414_OcellarisClownfish"},"Ssd":"20260414","Name":"OcellarisClownfish","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2121702907","FullDateString":"14 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"When the lights go down, the universe puts on a show. The image of the Milky Way glowing above Anza-Borrego Desert State Park captures that feeling perfectly. As California's largest state park and a certified International Dark-Sky Association Dark Sky Park, Anza-Borrego offers some of the clearest night skies in the country. On cloudless evenings, the heavens fill with planets, star clusters and the pale river of our home galaxy, a sight long lost to many city dwellers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_ROW1985712263_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BorregoStars_ROW1985712263_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Milky Way over Anza-Borrego Desert State Park, California, United States","Copyright":"© Kevin Key/Slworking)/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Anza+Borrego+Desert+State+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260413_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260413_BorregoStars"},"Ssd":"20260413","Name":"BorregoStars","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1985712263","FullDateString":"13 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Look up on a clear night and a bright moving star might actually be the International Space Station. That spirit of exploration lives on aboard the ISS, a laboratory where Earth never quite leaves the view. From the space station, astronauts photograph glowing city grids, curling auroras and lightning storms streaking through the atmosphere. The station orbits about 400 kilometres above Earth and circles the planet every 90 minutes, delivering up to 16 sunrises and sunsets each day.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_ROW1837084616_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpaceTrails_ROW1837084616_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"City lights streak below, taken from the International Space Station","Copyright":"© NASA","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Space+Station&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260412_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260412_SpaceTrails"},"Ssd":"20260412","Name":"SpaceTrails","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1837084616","FullDateString":"12 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"A beach born from fire rarely does so subtly, yet Papagayo Beach manages exactly that. The shoreline we see today rests on the southern edge of Lanzarote, one of Spain's Canary Islands. Tropical fantasy? More like volcanic precision. Millions of years ago, this land rose in successive layers of basalt and ash thrust upward by submarine eruptions.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_ROW1699824695_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PlayaPapagayo_ROW1699824695_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Papagayo Beach, Lanzarote, Canary Islands, Spain","Copyright":"© Gavin Hellier/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Lanzarote+Canary+Islands+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260411_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260411_PlayaPapagayo"},"Ssd":"20260411","Name":"PlayaPapagayo","Market":"ROW","Hash":"1699824695","FullDateString":"11 Apr 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What happens when water moves too slowly to notice? In Everglades National Park, it shapes everything. Covering around 6,100 square kilometres, the park was established in 1947 to protect a wetland system unlike any other in the United States. As a recognised UNESCO World Heritage Site, the park's elevated pinelands rise above the marshes and prairies that form one of the world's largest wetland systems.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_ROW9169451135_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_ROW9169451135_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Forest hammock of slash pine and saw palmetto, Everglades National Park, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Mary Liz Austin/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Everglades+National+Park+Florida&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260424_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine"},"Ssd":"20260424","Name":"SlashPine","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9169451135","FullDateString":"24 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Small, lively and instantly recognisable by its call: the chiffchaff is one of Germany's most common songbirds and a true harbinger of spring. As early as late February, the first males return from their winter quarters in the Mediterranean or south-western Europe and begin their distinctive song, which gives the species its name. This clear 'chiff-chaff, chiff-chaff' makes it easy to locate, even when it remains hidden in dense vegetation.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ChiffchaffSpring_ROW0928406195_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ChiffchaffSpring_ROW0928406195_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Common chiffchaff, Germany","Copyright":"© Andyworks/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260423_ChiffchaffSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Common+chiffchaff&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260423_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260423_ChiffchaffSpring"},"Ssd":"20260423","Name":"ChiffchaffSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0928406195","FullDateString":"23 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Take Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Estonia—what makes it so special? Established in 1994, it protects one of the country's largest and most intact wetland systems, where rivers like the Pedja and Põltsamaa still flow freely. The 342-square-kilometres reserve is a haven for wildlife. Moose roam the wetlands, lynx move through dense forests and rare birds such as the black stork and lesser spotted eagle nest in its quieter corners. With limited human settlement, much of the area remains untouched—no large-scale farming, no urban spread. Seasonal flooding reshapes the landscape, renewing habitats and sustaining rich biodiversity year after year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_ROW8518008837_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TartuEstonia_ROW8518008837_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Alam-Pedja Nature Reserve in Tartu County, Estonia","Copyright":"© Sven Zacek/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Alam+Pedja+Nature+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260422_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260422_TartuEstonia"},"Ssd":"20260422","Name":"TartuEstonia","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8518008837","FullDateString":"22 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring arrives with a small, spiky ambassador: the European hedgehog, spotted here in France. Part cuddle, part survival gear, this tiny forager is mostly nocturnal and usually solitary, guided mainly by smell and sound. Its job description is simple: roam, sniff through leaf litter and vacuum up invertebrates like worms, beetles, slugs and caterpillars—the kind of snacks that keep ecosystems running and gardeners smiling. When danger shows up, it doesn't negotiate or flee. It curls into a tight ball and lets its spines do the talking.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_ROW8347906365_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringHedgehog_ROW8347906365_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"European hedgehog, France","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=European+hedgehog&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260421_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260421_SpringHedgehog"},"Ssd":"20260421","Name":"SpringHedgehog","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8347906365","FullDateString":"21 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In south-eastern Utah, USA, Canyonlands National Park reveals a vast, rugged landscape shaped over millions of years by the Colorado and Green rivers. Established in 1964, the park protects a maze of canyons, mesas and buttes carved into layers of ancient rock. Divided into districts such as Island in the Sky and The Needles, it offers sweeping views that shift with the light from dawn to dusk.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_ROW8130256678_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunsetKiva_ROW8130256678_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Sunset in Canyonlands National Park, Moab, Utah, United States","Copyright":"© Jason Hatfield/Tandem Stills + Motion","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Canyonlands+National+Park+Moab&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260420_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260420_SunsetKiva"},"Ssd":"20260420","Name":"SunsetKiva","Market":"ROW","Hash":"8130256678","FullDateString":"20 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"From above, Brazil's Mirror Beach looks like a watercolour you can walk into. Pale cliffs, reefs stitched into the shoreline and a mosaic of tide pools that, at low tide, reflect the sky and clouds so clearly that the beach earns its name. Tucked into Bahia, a north-eastern state on the Atlantic coast, it sits between small fishing villages in the city of Porto Seguro. Access follows dirt roads and short trails—a natural crowd-control system that keeps the vibe intimate. For years, it stayed off the map, known only through word of mouth, until the 1990s brought it onto travellers' radars.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_ROW7860007942_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TranBA_ROW7860007942_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Mirror Beach, Porto Seguro, Bahia, Brazil","Copyright":"© Marcelo Nacinovic/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bahia+Brazil&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260419_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260419_TranBA"},"Ssd":"20260419","Name":"TranBA","Market":"ROW","Hash":"7860007942","FullDateString":"19 Apr 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Rolling hills in Tuscany, Italy, feel like they've been styled with intent—soft curves, neat rows of vines and those tall, unmistakable cypress trees. Have you ever noticed how the landscape seems to change colour with the seasons? Spring brings bright greens and wildflowers, summer turns fields golden and autumn deepens everything into warm, earthy tones.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ToscanaSpring_ROW0859656735_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ToscanaSpring_ROW0859656735_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Rolling hills of Tuscany, Italy","Copyright":"© Andyworks/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260418_ToscanaSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tuscany+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260418_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260418_ToscanaSpring"},"Ssd":"20260418","Name":"ToscanaSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0859656735","FullDateString":"18 Apr 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Image of the day","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Learn more","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donate now","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Quick fact:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Recent Homepage images","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Homepage image for {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"On this day in history","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"On this day in {0}, {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Share today's Bing homepage","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERDOWNLOAD_TOOLTIP":"Download this image. Use of this image is restricted to wallpaper only.","LOC_MUSCARD_DOWNLOAD_LINK":"Download this image","LOC_HOMEPAGE_WALLPAPERNOTAVAILABLE":"This image is not available to download as wallpaper.","LOC_HOMEPAGE_INFO_TEXT":"Info","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK":"https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2127455","LOC_BING_WP_APP_LINK_TEXT":"Get the Bing Wallpaper app","LOC_BING_APP_TEXT":"Get Bing Wallpaper on your devices","LOC_BING_APP_LINK_PC":"https://bing.microsoftapp.net/bing/?adjust=nk9xri2_dzfz5n2","LOC_BING_APP_LINK_MOBILE":"https://app.adjust.com/d93ddtl_a75k0gg?deeplink=sapphire%3A%2F%2Fwallpaper","LOC_BING_APP_DOWNLOAD_TEXT":"Mobile App","LOC_BING_WP_APP_DOWNLOAD_TEXT":"Desktop App","LOC_BING_APP_TEXT_MOBILE":"Get daily photos with Bing App","LOC_BING_APP_DOWNLOAD_TEXT_MOBILE":"Get","LOC_